{
  "stem": "21310.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But they had to pay the farmer to take the horse.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the farmer promised that he's going to feed the horse.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My father walked all the way till he met with the advancing Soviet army because Hitler made the pact with Stalin before the war to divide Poland.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And as he met the Soviet army, he didn't like what he saw.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he certainly didn't want to be under the Soviets.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So he turned around and was coming back.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "On the way, he got extremely sick.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And somebody had seen him when he was so sick, and they came and-- and told us that they had seen my father but that he had survived the original shooting but that he was very sick.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we still didn't know if he lived or not.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But he did come back later after the German-- the Germans occupied Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, during the bombardment, my-- we lived on-- well, we lived on the fifth floor, and the electricity was out so thereon the elevator didn't work anymore.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my mother had-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] had the keys to an apartment in-- on the first floor.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she thought-- it belonged to a friend of hers who had left.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so she decided to take some of our more valuable stuff-- like the winter coats and some food that she had because she used to can fruit and, I don't remember, vegetables, but mostly fruit like cherries and like applesauce.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so she-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] she was taking that stuff down.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was taking it down from the fifth floor to the-- to the first floor.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she was arranging them, all that stuff, in the bathroom, which was all tiled and--",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
